Evelyn Murray-Bruce, wife to former lawmaker representing Bayelsa East in the upper legislative chamber, Senator Ben Murray-Bruce, is dead.
The 41-year-old Evelyn was battling cancer before her death. Bruce disclosed this on his Twitter page even as he expressed sadness over her death. Bruce wrote: “ I’m broken. Just lost my beautiful wife to cancer. She was my best friend for 43 years and my wife for 41 years. “Cancer is real, but it shouldn’t be a death sentence – awareness, and early detection and treatment are key to survival. “I miss her so so much. I’m broken.”